The '''Academy of Sciences, Humanities and Arts of Lyon''' (French: Académie des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts de Lyon) is a [[France |French]] [[learned society]] founded in 1700.<ref name="ss">{{cite web |title=Académie des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts de Lyon |url=http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/1700asblal.html |website=Scholarly Societies Project |publisher=University of Waterloo |accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref> The founders were:
* [[Claude Brossette]], lawyer, alderman of Lyons, and administrator of the [[Hôtel-Dieu de Lyon]];
* [[Laurent Dugas]], President of the [[Cour des monnaies]];
* {{ill|Camille Falconet|fr}}, future consulting physician of King [[Louis XIV]] and member of the [[Académie des Inscriptions et Belles-Lettres]];
* Antoine de Serre, adviser to the Cour des monnaies;
* Louis de Puget, naturalist;
* Father Jean de Saint-Bonnet,{{efn|Apparently a different figure than {{ill|Jean de Saint-Bonnet|es}}}} professor at Trinity College;{{efn|It is not clear which Trinity College this refers to; There was no Trinity College in France in this era.}}
* Thomas Bernard Fellon.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |first1= Patrice |last1 = Béghain |first2 = Bruno |last2 = Benoit |first3 = Gérard |last3 = Corneloup |first4 = Bruno |last4 = Thévenon (coord.) |title = Dictionnaire historique de Lyon |editor = Stéphane Bachès |location = Lyons |year = 2009 |isbn = 9782915266658 |language=fr}}</ref>

It appears to have continued to be active, with some intermissions,<ref name="ss"/> until at least 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title=Archived Documents |url=http://academiedelyon.nexenservices.com/page_archives.html |website=Academy of Lyon |publisher=Academy of Lyon |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017170320/http://academiedelyon.nexenservices.com/page_archives.html |archivedate=17 October 2013 |location=Lyons, France |language=French}}</ref>

