'''Jonas Coersmeier''' is an award-winning [[architect]] and [[designer]], born in Germany and working in the United States. He is [[Final (competition)|finalist]] and first [[runner-up]] in the [[World Trade Center Memorial Competition]]. He was born in [[Cologne, Germany]] and studied architecture at [[Columbia University]], [[M.I.T.]] and [[Technical University Darmstadt]]. He teaches at the [[Pratt Institute School of Architecture]], where he coordinates the Architecture and Urban Design program (MSAUD,) [[University of Pennsylvania School of Design]] and [[University of Kassel]] School of Architecture, where he was head of the Digital Design Department.<ref name=wtc>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtcsitememorial.org/fin2_bio.html |title=World Trade Center Memorial Site: Finalist profiles|publisher=Lower Manhattan Development Corporation (wtcsitememorial.org)}}</ref>
